<h2 id="comments">Comments</h2>

<div id="c1">
<p>A website I built (years ago, using web.py) - http://traveldk.com/ - gives users the tools to build custom travel guides. Maybe that would be a good place to start? I can contribute some info for the UK and Palestine.</p>

<p class="posted">posted by <a rel="nofollow" href="http://intellectronica.net/">Tom Berger</a>
 on September  4, 2011 <a href="#c1" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
</div>
<div id="c2">
<p>Hi, maybe you like Mediamatic Travel (http://travel.mediamatic.net/). They have their focus on the things that you don&#8217;t read in the tourist books.</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>The Mediamatic Travel website acts as a network of cultural professionals from all over the world. It provides an open platform where they can exchange information about the unseen or underground culture in their city. Things you normally won&#8217;t find in your average travel agency.</p>
</blockquote>

<p class="posted">posted by Lode Claassen
 on September  4, 2011 <a href="#c2" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
